Package: Replication
Type: Package
Title: Test Replications by Means of the Prior Predictive p-Value
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person(c("M.A.J."), "Zondervan-Zwijnenburg", role = c("aut","cre"), email = "m.a.j.zwijnenburg@uu.nl"),
    person(c("Herbert"), "Hoijtink", role = c("ths"), email = "h.hoijtink@uu.nl"),
    person(c("Caspar", "J"), "van Lissa", role = c("ctb"), email = "c.j.vanlissa@uu.nl"),
    person("Consortium Individual Development", role = "fnd", comment="NWO grant number 024.001.003")
    )
Description: Allows for the computation of a prior predictive p-value to test replication of relevant features of original studies. Relevant features are captured in informative hypotheses. The package also allows for the computation of power. The statistical underpinnings are described in Zondervan-Zwijnenburg (2019) <doi:10.31234/osf.io/uvh5s>.
License: GPL (>= 3)
Depends: lavaan(>= 0.6-3), blavaan, mice
Imports: quadprog, graphics, MASS, runjags(>= 2.0.4-2), rjags
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
